			<dd class="lead"><a href="/sports/cycling/story/2012/08/30/sp-cycling-tyler-hamilton-lance-armstrong-tour-de-france-performance-enhancing-drugs.html">Tyler Hamilton says Lance Armstrong gave him an illegal blood booster at his house before the 1999 Tour de France and the two teammates compared notes on using performance-enhancing drugs as far back as 1998.</a> <a href="/sports/cycling/story/2012/08/30/sp-cycling-tyler-hamilton-lance-armstrong-tour-de-france-performance-enhancing-drugs.html" class="more">more <span>&raquo;</span></a></dd>
		</dl>
	</div>

	<div class="morestories">
	<dl>
		
		<dt class="headline"><a href="/sports/cycling/story/2012/08/29/sp-lance-armstrong-cycling-usada-cancer-conference.html">Defiant Lance Armstrong: 'I won Tour de France 7 times'</a> <span class="mediaicons"><img src="/includes/gfx/icon_video.gif" border="0" class="mediaicons-vid" alt="Video" /></span> <span class="socialicons" title="2000528574"></span>
		</dt>
		<dd class="lead">Lance Armstrong defiantly introduced himself to a cancer conference in Montreal today as a seven-time Tour de France champion. <a href="/sports/cycling/story/2012/08/29/sp-lance-armstrong-cycling-usada-cancer-conference.html" class="more">more <span>&raquo;</span></a></dd>
		
		<dt class="headline"><a href="/sports/cycling/story/2012/08/28/sp-lance-armstrong-foundation.html">Lance Armstrong Foundation sees donations jump since his announcement</a> <span class="socialicons" title="2000528477"></span>
		</dt>
		<dd class="lead">Lance Armstrong's reputation may be permanently stained but in the eyes of corporate and individual donors, his charity still wears an unsullied yellow jersey. <a href="/sports/cycling/story/2012/08/28/sp-lance-armstrong-foundation.html" class="more">more <span>&raquo;</span></a></dd>
		
		<dt class="headline"><a href="/sports/cycling/story/2012/08/25/sp-cycling-lance-armstrong-us-anti-doping-agency-ban.html">'Nobody needs to cry for me': Lance Armstrong</a> <span class="socialicons" title="2000527918"></span>
		</dt>
		<dd class="lead">In his first interview since the U.S. Anti-Doping Agency disciplined Lance Armstrong with a lifetime ban from professional cycling and vacated his seven Tour de France titles, he said, "Nobody needs to cry for me. I'm going to be great." <a href="/sports/cycling/story/2012/08/25/sp-cycling-lance-armstrong-us-anti-doping-agency-ban.html" class="more">more <span>&raquo;</span></a></dd>
		
		<dt class="headline"><a href="/sports/cycling/story/2012/08/24/sp-usada-cycling-lance-armstrong.html">Lance Armstrong stripped of Tour de France titles by USADA</a> <span class="mediaicons"><img src="/includes/gfx/icon_video.gif" border="0" class="mediaicons-vid" alt="Video" /></span> <span class="socialicons" title="2000527638"></span>
		</dt>
		<dd class="lead">The U.S. Anti-Doping Agency has stripped Lance Armstrong's seven Tour de France titles, erasing one of the most incredible achievements in sports after deciding he had used performance-enhancing drugs to do it. <a href="/sports/cycling/story/2012/08/24/sp-usada-cycling-lance-armstrong.html" class="more">more <span>&raquo;</span></a></dd>
		
	</dl>
